snippet.textDisplay: Good songs. But I don't understand is it mandatory to use folk/lalon Kind of songs always??? Expecting band music like warfaze/miles/LRB and pop music like that of tahsan/arnob/minar solo. That was our modern bangladeshi culture. Songs like nasek nasek is not bangla or doesn't represent our modern culture. Lolon/folk songs are OK, however, Coke studio already used it many times and now we are thinking, is it mandatory to use as per coke studio rules, that it must have to be folk/lalon?. We need 90s and 2000s vibe with band and pop music, our modern bangladeshi culture.

snippet.textDisplay:
No offence but Using saxophone in every song, is not obvious. Specially in Lalon songs. Doesn’t mean we don't like fusionism, but there are certain music connected with our root, needs to be modernised with our very own native musical instruments. People, around the world, have started knowing Bengali culture by listening coke studio (all thanks to CSB creator team). They should know how baul sing with, how Bhatiyali sing with, what instruments are used in moimonsingha gitika etc. I recall some reactors of different countries  were wondering about Ek Tara after watching the intro song. It really feels special & proud. 
(My intention is not to criticize anyone. Just expressing my opinion as a CSB fan).
